Regionalization of the ow duration curves for total and seasonal periods in
Santa Catarina state, Brazil: a geostatistical approach based on models
Regionalizao de curvas de permanncia de vazo para perodos
total e sazonal no Estado de Santa Catarina, Brasil: uma
abordagem geoestatstica baseada em modelos
Wagner Wol

University of So Paulo.
Abstract
Flow duration curves (FDCs) represent the percentage of time (or duration) during which a given stream-
ow was equaled or exceeded over the historical period. FDCs provide a rapid and direct response to the
behavior of water resources in a watershed. Thus, predicting or regionalizing FDCs is important in basins
with little or no monitoring for both total and seasonal periods. The geostatistical approach for region-
alization of FDCs is the state of the art in this area of knowledge. However, current approaches do not
address model based geostatistics and an assessment by likelihood criteria for trend removal and verication
of spatial dependence. The aim of this work is to regionalize the FDCs in a total and seasonal period for
Santa Catarina state, Brazil, using a geostatistical approach based on models. Data from streamgage made
available by the National Water Agency (ANA) were used. These stations have regular distribution and
high density within the state. For spatialize the FDCs and, consequently, all their permanency streamows,
a geostatistical modeling of the scale and shape parameters of the FDCs was made. Initially, some basic
assumptions for the FDCs parameters such as data normality and spatial stationarity were veried. After
accepting the assumptions it was veried through statistical tests regarding its likelihood, if the structure of
spatial dependence of the geostatistical model increase its performance, justifying the use of this structure for
the FDCs paramenters spatialization. To check the assumptions of good prediction, the residue dispersion of
the spatial interpolations was evaluated through cross-validation. The results showed a better performance
for the geostatiscal models with the spatial dependence structure, both for period total and seasonal of the
FDCs. Thus, these models were used to the spatial interpolation, observing a good prediction through the
residue dispersion. This work contributes to a better spatial representation of FDCs in Santa Catarina state,
since it is based on likelihood criteria to choose models that better represent the phenomenon studied in
space.

1. Introduction1
The ow duration curves (FDCs) graphically represents the percentage of time, or duration, in which the2
streamow has been equaled or exceeded over a historical period (Vogel and Fennessey, 1994). The FDCs can3
have two hydrological viewpoints. A deterministic, in which the FDCs represented the hydrological behavior4
of the watersheds, as a result of the integration among climate, morphology and soil permeability. In terms5
statistical, the FDCs are empirically represented by probability distribution adjusted to streamow historical6
series. Through survivor function of these distributions is estimated a streamow for a given probability of7
the equaling or exceeding an event (Castellarin, 2014).8
2
As curvas de permanncia de vazo (CPVs) representam gracamente o tempo, ou durao,9
durante o qual uma dada vazo igualada ou excedida em determinado perodo (Vogel and10
Fennessey, 1994). As CPVs podem ter dois pontos de vista em termos hidrolgicos, um de-11
terminstico e outro estatstico. Deterministicamente as CPVs representam o comportamento12
hidrolgico de uma bacia hidrogrca, como resultado da interao entre clima, morfologia,13
e uso e ocupao do solo. Por sua vez, estatisticamente as CPVs so representadas empiri-14
camente por distribuies de probabilidade ajustadas s sries histricas de vazo, nas quais,15
mediante a funo sobrevivncia dessas distribuies, estimada uma vazo para uma dada16
probabilidade de igualdade ou excedncia (Castellarin, 2014).17
Even though some variations exists, FDCs in general was made by daily streamow, and consider either18
each year individually or the entire period of record. In this work is focused to daily FDCs for all sampled19
period and for seasonal periods, in which are important for design and water supply systems, irrigation20
planning and management, waste load allocation, sedimentation studies, hydropower generation, among21
others (Vogel and Fennessey, 1995). Moreover, by knowing of the FDCs is possible determinate the stremows22
that are reference for the granting of permits to the exploitation and use of water resources in Brazil and in23
the state of Santa Catarina.24
Embora existam algumas variaes, as CPVs geralmente so formadas por vazes dirias,25
e consideram cada ano individualmente ou todo o perodo amostrado conjuntamente. Neste26
trabalho dado enfoque as CPVs dirias para todo o perodo amostrado e para perodos27
sazonais, os quais so importantes para projetos e sistemas de abastecimento de gua, planeja-28
mento e gesto da irrigao, alocao de carga de resduos, estudos de sedimentao, potencial29
hidreltrico, entre outros (Vogel and Fennessey, 1995). Alm disso, pelo conhecimento das30
CPVs possvel determinar as vazes que so referncias para a outorga de recursos hdricos;31
esse um dos instrumentos de leis que tangem o manejo e a gesto adequada dos recursos32
hdricos no Brasil e no Estado de Santa Catarina.33
Once the FDCs provide an important characterization of streamows magnitude in a watershed, contin-34
uous streamows measurements are required. However, due the nonexistence of the monitoring, the stream-35
ows data are not make available for all drainage system. In general, areas in which the stremows are not36
measures are areas with more problems at a hydrological viewpoint and, thus, the knowing of streamow37
behavior is more important for these areas.38
Uma vez que as CPVs fornecem uma caracterizao importante da magnitude das vazes39
em uma bacia hidrogrca, essas necessitam de dados de vazo dos cursos d gua medidos40
continuamente. Entretanto, devido a falta de monitoramento os dados de vazo no esto41
disponveis para toda a rede de drenagem. Geralmente, reas nas quais as vazes no so42
monitoradas so as reas mais problemticas do ponto de vista hidrolgico e, assim, so aquelas43
em que o conhecimento do comportamento das vazes mais importante.44
3
Therefore, due this necessity, FDCs regionalization have been an intense research eld (NERC, 1975;45
Li et al., 2010; Costa et al., 2014; Pugliese et al., 2014, 2016). Through the growing concern with the46
predictions in sites without monitoring, International Association of Hydrological Sciences (IAHS) promoted47
an initiative to encourage forecasting studies in basins without monitoring, called of Predictions in Ungauged48
Basins (PUB) (Sivapalan et al., 2003). FDCs regionalization was one of the main aims of PUB, due to its49
large use on water resources planing and management.50
Portanto, diante dessa necessidade, a regionalizao de CPVs tem sido uma rea de pesquisa51
intensa (NERC, 1975; Li et al., 2010; Costa et al., 2014; Pugliese et al., 2014, 2016). Dada a52
crescente preocupao com a previso de vazes em locais sem monitoramento, a International53
Association of Hydrological Sciences (IAHS) promoveu uma iniciativa para incentivar estudos de54
previses em bacias sem monitoramento, denominado de Predictions in Ungauged Basins (PUB)55
(Sivapalan et al., 2003). A regionalizao de CPVs em locais sem monitoramento foi um dos56
principais objetivos da PUB, devido sua grande utilizao no planejamento, manejo e gesto57
de recursos hdricos.58
Concerning prediction of the FDCs in sites without monitoring, in literature are approached some methods59
(Castellarin, 2014). Among the approaches, the more used is the regionalization by regression regional60
equations, both for estimate the quantiles and parameters of probabilistic models that represent the FDCs61
(Mohamoud, 2008; Li et al., 2010; Longobardi and Villani, 2013; Costa et al., 2014). The disadvantage of62
this methodology is the need to delimit hydrologically homogeneous regions. Moreover, due to many physical63
and climatic variables that aect the water regime of a basin, regional model estimates generate uncertainties64
(Castellarin et al., 2007).65
Com relao a predio das CPVs em locais sem monitoramento, existem na literatura66
diferentes abordagens para esse m (Castellarin, 2014). Dentre as abordagens existentes, a mais67
utilizada a que utiliza equaes regionais de regresso, tanto para estimar os quantis quanto68
os parmetros de modelos probabilsticos que representam as CPVs (Mohamoud, 2008; Li et al.,69
2010; Longobardi and Villani, 2013; Costa et al., 2014). A desvantagem desta metodologia 70
o fato de ser previamente necessrio a delimitao de regies hidrologicamente semelhantes.71
Alm disso, devido a diferentes tipos de variveis fsicas e climticas que condicionam o regime72
hdrico de uma bacia, as estimativas por modelos regionais geram incertezas (Castellarin et al.,73
2007).74
In turn, geostatistical approaches are interesting, once the identication of the hydrologically homogeneous75
regions is not necessary, while is used regional hydrological information, to interpolate this information in76
ungauged basins (Skien et al., 2005; Mller and Thompson, 2015). Regarding the FDCs regionalization77
through geostatistical approaches, the method proposed by Pugliese et al. (2014) is considered the state of78
the art. Pugliese et al. (2014) uses the top-kring method (Skien et al., 2005) to spatially interpolate FDCs79
standardized by the long-term annual mean streamow (Q) and, thus, estimate the FDCs in sites without80
4
monitoring. The method aforementioned is better than the multivariate regression method, once it need just81
of streamow historical series information (Pugliese et al., 2016).82
Neste contexto, as abordagens geostatsticas tm demonstrado ser ecazes em dispensar83
a identicao preliminar de regies hidrologicamente homogneas, ao mesmo tempo em que84
utilizam informaes hidrolgicas regionais, para regionalizar as mesmas em bacias no mon-85
itoradas (Skien et al., 2005; Mller and Thompson, 2015). Com relao a regionalizao de86
CPVs por abordagens geoestatsticas o mtodo proposto por Pugliese et al. (2014) tido como87
o estado atual da arte. Pugliese et al. (2014) utilizaram o mtodo top-kriging (Skien et al., 2005)88
para interpolar espacialmente CPVs normalizadas pela vazo mdia plurianual (Q) e, assim,89
estimar as CPVs em locais sem monitoramento. Em comparao com o mtodo de regresso90
multivariada dos quantis de vazo, o mtodo supracitado favorvel, uma vez que necessita91
apenas de informao das sries histricas de vazo (Pugliese et al., 2016).92
However, as Pugliese et al. (2014) method uses FDCs standardized by Q is necessary to regionalize the Q93
using regression equations. Thus, the justication to use a geostatistical approach can not be valid. Moreover,94
Pugliese et al. (2016) concluded that this method has a poor performance for regions with high mean annual95
temperature, low mean elevation, low run-o ratio and high potential evapotranspiration ratio. This occur96
because in these regions the local mean is signicantly dierent of the global mean. Thus, a spatial trend97
is observed and the interpolation generate poor estimates. To resolve these problems and to promote an98
evolution in this area of knowledge, we propose a regionalization of CPVs parameters standardized by the99
watershed areas, using a geostatistical approach based on models, and in the maximum likelihood to evaluate100
removal trend and spatial dependence.101
Entretanto, como o mtodo de Pugliese et al. (2014) utiliza CPVs padronizadas pela Q,102
necessrio regionalizar a Q por equaes de regresso e, assim, a justicativa de usar uma103
abordagem geoestatstica pode no ser vlida. Alm disso, Pugliese et al. (2016) concluram104
que este mtodo tem um mal desempenho para regies caracterizadas por alta temperatura105
mdia anual, baixa elevao mdia, baixa razo de escoamento supercial e elevado potencial106
de evapotranspirao. Isso ocorre pelo fato de que nessas regies a mdia local difere signi-107
camente da mdia global e, assim, a interpolao espacial acaba sendo tendenciosa e gerando108
estimativas ruins. Neste enfoque, para contornar estes problemas e promover evoluo nesta109
rea do conhecimento, foi proposto uma regionalizao dos parmetros das CPVs padronizadas110
pelas reas das bacias de drenagem, por meio de uma abordagem geoestatstica baseada em111
modelos, e na verossimilhana para avaliar a remoo de tendncia e a dependncia espacial.112
Diggle and Ribeiro (2007) proposed a geostatiscal approach based in Gaussian stationary models, in113
which the parameters adjustment are performed by statistical inference methods based on likelihood function114
obtained from a multivariate Gaussian distribution. This approach is advantageous because the adjustment115
is performed directly to the data, and not to an empiric semivariogram, as done by the least squares method.116

Besides that, the model evaluation can be performed by a more parsimonious statistical test considering117
the likelihood despite the cross-validation, which is not a hypothesis test but a method to check the residue118
dispersion caused by the spatial interpolation (Davis, 1987).119

feita por um teste estatstico mais parcimonioso, considerando a verossimilhana, ao invs da127

Therefore, in this work we proposed test the hypothesis in which, through the addition of the component130

scale and shape of FDCs parameters. The aim of work is to interpolate spatially the FDCs, considering total132
and seasonal periods for Santa Catarina state, Brazil, through an geostatiscal approach based on models.133
Portanto, neste estudo prope-se testar a hiptese de que, ao acrescentar o componente134
espacialmente correlacionado em um modelo geoestatstico, esse represente uma melhor ca-135
pacidade para modelar no espao os parmetros de escala e de forma das CPVs. O objetivo136
nal do trabalho o de regionalizar as CPVs, considerando os perodos total e sazonais para137
o Estado de Santa Catarina, Brasil, por meio de uma abordagem geoestatstica baseada em138

The gap lling at the daily streamow data was done by data imputation techniques, which consists of189
lling the missing data of a database, through statistical methodologies.190
O preenchimento de falhas nas sries dirias de vazo foi feito pela tcnica de imputao191
de dados, que consiste em preencher os dados faltantes de um banco de dados, por meio de192
metodologias estatsticas.193
Ruiz-Crdenas and Krainski (2011) tested some methodologies for gap lling. They concluded that for194
daily meteorological databases, the methodology which uses the EM algorithm (expectation-maximization)195
was the best.196
Testando diferentes metodologias, Ruiz-Crdenas and Krainski (2011) concluram que para197
o preenchimento de falhas em bancos de dados meteorolgicos dirios, a metodologia na qual198
utiliza o algoritmo EM (Esperana Maximizada) foi a melhor.199
In additon to considering the correlation structure between the stations used for the data covariance200
matrix, the methodology also considers the temporal correlation, through independent modelling of the time201
series in each station (Junger and de Leon, 2015).202

feature of this choice is emphasized by (Wackernagel, 2003); according to the author, the OK is an exact492
interpolator, thus, for an estimation of a variable in an already sampled location, the estimated value will493
be equal to the sample.494
Aps a escolha do modelo e estimativa de seus parmetros, a Krigagem Ordinria (KO) foi495

no viciada e com mnima varincia (BLUE = Best Linear Unbiased Estimator); essas propriedades497
so denidas como: (i) linear, suas estimativas so combinaes lineares ponderadas dos498
dados disponveis; (ii) no viciada, busca o valor do erro ou resduo mdio igual a 0; e,499
(iii) melhor, porque minimiza a varincia dos erros (Isaaks and Srivastava, 1989). Outra500
caracterstica para esta escolha enfatizada por (Wackernagel, 2003); segundo o autor, a KO501
um exato interpolador, sendo que, para uma estimativa de uma varivel em um local j502

Finally, the Leave-one-out cross-validation (LOOCV) was performed, where each data location is removed512
from the data set and the variable at this location is predicted using the remaining locations, for a given513
model. According to (Davis, 1987) the LOOCV does not arm if a model is better than another, because it is514
not a hypothesis test method, but an exploratory method to comprehend the phenomenon on the studied area.515
Therefore, to verify if the spatial interpolation was admissible, according to the assumptions of normality516
and homocedasticity residues, a residual graphical analysis was performed.517

The presented results support the importance of the hydrogeological characteristics with baseow index911
(BFI) in the geostatistical modeling of FDCs scale parameter and, consequently, in the streamow regional-912
ization. Previous studies support the importance of BFI (Longobardi and Villani, 2013; Atieh et al., 2015;913
Javeed and Apoorva, 2015).914
Os resultados apresentados reforam a importncia da caracterizao hidrogeolgica pelo915
ndice de escoamento de base (BFI), na modelagem geoestatstica do parmetro de escala das916
CPVs e, consequentemente, na regionalizao de vazes. Estudos anteriores do suporte a917
importncia do BFI (Longobardi and Villani, 2013; Atieh et al., 2015; Javeed and Apoorva,918
2015).919
36
In this study, the BFI was used in models to remove spatial trends and, consequently, the spatial predic-920
tions was performed using the residuals of these models, which is named of universal kriging (KU). The use921
of this methodology allows that the BFI does not need to be previously determined to obtain the permanence922
streamows. Therefore, the proposed methodology is more parsimonious, compared to the methodologies923
that use regression equations of the variables related to the characteristics of the watersheds, such as the924
annual average rainfall, drainage density and shape factor.925
Neste estudo, o BFI foi utilizado em modelos para remoo de tendncias espaciais e,926
consequentemente, a predio espacial foi realizada utilizando os resduos desses modelos, o927
qual denominada de krigagem universal (KU). O uso desta metodologia permite que o BFI928
no precise ser previamente determinado para obteno das vazes de permanncia e, assim, a929
metodologia proposta mais parcimoniosa, comparada s metodologias que utilizam equaes930
de regresso em funo de variveis relacionadas s caractersticas das bacias de drenagem,931
como por exemplo a precipitao mdia anual, a densidade de drenagem e o fator de forma da932
bacia.933

Uma vez que foi observada uma maior densidade nas classes centrais e menor nos extremos,954
37
conclui-se que a distribuio dos resduos para todos os parmetros das CPVs tende a normal-955
idade. Assim, como a pressuposio de homoscedasticidade, a pressuposio de normalidade956
foi aceita, conferindo uma estimativa satisfatria.957
In this study the LOOCV was used to verify the good prediction of geostatistical model and not to958
compare and select the respective model, once direct methods based in the likelihood were used to make959
this work. Therefore, the results of the LOOCV area in acceptation with the methodology to select the best960
models.961
Neste estudo a VC foi utilizada para vericar a aceitao da predio do modelo geoes-962
tatstico e no para comparar e selecionar o respectivo modelo, uma vez que foram utilizados963
mtodos diretos baseados na verossimilhana para esse m. Portanto, os resultados da VC964
conrmaram a metodologia para seleo dos melhores modelos.965

4. Conclusions966
The present study shows the rst application of a geostatistical approach based in models, aiming at967
spatializing the ow duration curve (FDCs) for the total and seasonal periods in the state of Santa Cata-968
rina, Brazil. In total 83 streamgages were used, distributed regularly at the state. The total and seasonal969
representation of the FDCs allowed a best knowing of seasonal dynamic of important streamows for the970
authorization of water resources use, such as the streamow with 98% of permanence on time standardized971
by area (Q
98esp
). The main conclusions of this study can by summarized as follows:972
Neste estudo foi apresentado a primeira aplicao de uma abordagem geoestatstica baseada973
em modelos na espacializao de curvas de permanncia de vazes (CPVs) para os perodos total974
e sazonais, para as estaes de vero, outono, inverno e primavera no Estado de Santa Catarina,975
Brasil. Ao todo foram utilizados 83 estaes uviomtricas, distribudas regularmente sobre976
o Estado. A representao completa e sazonal das CPVs permitiu um melhor conhecimento977
da dinmica sazonal das vazes importantes para a outorga de recursos hdricos superciais,978
como por exemplo a vazo especca com 98% de permanncia no tempo (Q
98esp
). As principais979
concluses deste estudo podem ser resumidas, como segue:980
i. Through the non spatial data exploratory analysis, we observed that was not necessary to normalize981
of the FDCs parameters. Although a positive asymmetry was observed for the shape parameter in summer982
period, this asymmetry did not interfered signicantly in the predictions of this variable;983
i. Pela anlise exploratria no espacial dos dados, foi observado que no foi necessrio984
a normalizao desses. Embora, tenha sido vericado certa assimetria para o parmetro de985
forma no perodo de vero, essa assimetria no interferiu signicativamente nas predies dessa986
varivel;987
ii. For the spatial exploratory analysis, we observed by the use of Akaike information criterion (AIC),988
method to choose models based in maximum likelihood, that all FDCs parameters had spatial trend, which989
was removed through regression models with 22 covariates from rainfall, morphometrical, hydrogelogical and990
hydrogracal and of the longitude and latitude, having in all 24 covariates. These models represent the991
deterministic component (
xi
) of the respective geostatistical models (Equation 6);992
ii. Para a anlise exploratria espacial, foi vericado pela utilizao do critrio de infor-993
mao de Akaike (AIC), mtodo de escolha de modelos baseado na verossimilhana, que todos994
os parmetros das CPVs tiveram tendncias espaciais, que foram removidas por modelos de re-995
gresso em funo de 22 covariveis oriundas das caracterizaes pluviomtrica, morfomtrica,996
hidrogeolgica e hidrogrca e da longitude e latitude, tendo ao todo 24 covariveis. Estes997
modelos representam o componente determinstico (
xi
) dos respectivos modelos geoestatsti-998
cos (Equao 6);999
iii. Adding the spatially correlated random factor (S
xi
) in the geostatistical models for all FDCs param-1000
eters, ensured the choice of models with better predictive capacity when compared to models without this1001

factor, according to the AIC test;1002
iii. O acrscimo do fator aleatrio espacialmente correlacionado (S

iv. The generated maps were conrmed by climatologic and hydrogeologic concepts, observing that the1006
main climatological factors that condition the Q
98esp
is the presence of two aquifers, that are the Serra Geral1007
